---

Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1/2}. Halve lengthways, then
thinly slice half (double for 4p).

Trim the @courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop into 1cm chunks.

Roughly chop the @parsley{5%g} stalks and all.

Drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1%pack} in a #sieve{}.

Place a large #pot{} for the chilli over a medium-high heat. Add a drizzle of 
@oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the chopped leek and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Cook the leek until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Add the @Irish pork mince{250%g} and fry until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season 
with salt and pepper.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The meat 
> is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add half the @Italian herbs{1/2%sachet} (double for 4p), courgette and 
cannellini beans to the pot. Cook for ~{1%minute}, stirring often.

Add @tomato paste{1%pack}, @vegetable stock{1%sachet} and @water{500%ml} 
(double for 4p).

Bring to a boil and simmer for ~{10-12%minutes}, or until the vegetables are 
tender.

Stir in the @dried chilli flakes{1%sachet} (use less if you don't like spice).

Season to taste with salt, pepper and @sugar{to taste}.

Dish up spoonfuls of hearty chilli.

Garnish with chopped parsley and @grated cheese{50%g}.